paragraph
 COMTRAN (COMmercial TRANslator) is an early programming language developed at IBM.  It was intended as the business programming equivalent of the scientific programming language FORTRAN (FORmula TRANslator).  It served as one of the forerunners to the COBOL language. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/COMTRAN">Read more on Wikipedia...</a>

